Subject:    domains and personal machines
From:       <a href="?a=95837784200016&r=1&w=2">schoff () csv ! rpi ! edu (Martin Schoffstall)</a>
Date:       <a href="?l=namedroppers&r=1&w=2&b=198612">1986-12-18 17:33:17</a></font>
[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837759026837&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837759026837&q=raw">body</a>]</b>


Quite a few people have personal machines that can
participate in the domain system.  Many of us have
affiliations so that we can appear under standards
like:

	schoff@vosburg-road.rpi.edu

But what happens to me if I go work for Dairy Queen
making malts, and I still want to participate?  Or
maybe I already work for Dairy Queen.

One potential "solution" for these (predominately uucp)
sites would be to join some non-profit corporation like
USENET.  Then we could appear maybe geographically within
that domain:

	schoff@vosburg-road.upstate.ny.usenix.org

Comments?  And maybe an organization to volunteer to do this?

Marty Schoffstall

